# The Heart System · ♥ — the NES ladder: points become moves

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of The Heart System](heart-system.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (The Heart System's organic-form embodiment): heart-system.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** The Heart System — ♥ — the NES ladder: points become moves

**what —** the NES port's progression — roughly every thousand points adds a heart, and each heart unlocks a new technique, up to seven

**where —** DDN · Double Dragon — Technōs Japan, arcade 1987 / NES 1988  Framework inputs: Double Dragon; the Lee brothers; Sōsetsuken; Marian; the Black Warriors  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** It is the cartridge's own invention: the machine teaching the fighter to grow, move by earned move — a thing the arcade never had.

**how —** Crystallized from Double Dragon (Technōs Japan): the 1987 arcade and the 1988 NES port.

**◌ the mythos —** It is the cartridge's own invention: the machine teaching the fighter to grow, move by earned move — a thing the arcade never had. a being of the ruined city and the long walk east

**the moniker —** ⟦The Heart System:DDN:435441⟧ · spoken *rurn-grur-gros*

**the seal —** ♥ — the NES ladder: points become moves

